Introduction [id=fba3_intro_section]
------------

::fba3_introduction [display=target:psych_sba_sidebar4auto label="View Introduction"]

Lin: So how did the intervention go with your roommate?

Annie: Thanks for asking! My roommate read our intervention plan. She tracked his progress in her journal. Over the past 2 weeks, she babysat 5 times. He went to bed on time 2 of the 5 occasions. On one of those occasions where he did not go to bed on time, she noted that she did not exactly follow our plan. In fact, the escape behaviors seem to have gotten worse over time! [face=worried]

JJ: That doesn't sound good at all. [face=concerned]

Progress Monitoring [id=fba3_progress_section]
-------------------

::fba3_predict_fidelity [display=target:psych_sba_sidebar4auto label="View Progress Data"]

--- wait @fba3_interpretation_confidence.value ---

Lin: Let's talk to our professor to find more resources to help improve the plan.

Annie: We showed the graph to the professor and explained that the roommate admitted she did not follow all of the consequence strategies.

Lianne: Looks like you need to improve on implementation fidelity. [face=serious]

Implementation Fidelity [id=fba3_fidelity_section]
------------------------

Lin: Okay, our professor gave us lots of good resources. Intervention fidelity refers to how accurately and consistently a behavior plan is implemented as it was designed.

JJ: In other words, was Annie's roommate doing what our plan says they should do? [face=explaining]

::fba3_fidelity_tabs [display=target:psych_sba_sidebar4auto label="Practice Fidelity Concepts"]

Annie: Now we're getting somewhere! Let me text my roommate to see exactly where things went wrong...

Fidelity Check [id=fba3_fidelity_check_section]
---------------

::fba3_fidelity_check [display=target:psych_sba_sidebar4auto label="Diagnose the Fidelity Issue"]

Annie: My roommate got back to me! She said that sometimes she forgets to do the warning countdown and timer, she forgets the small bedtime reward, and often falls into negotiating or arguing when he whines for extended time.

--- wait @fba3_fidelity_choice.submitCount > 0 ---

Improving Adherence [id=fba3_adherence_section]
--------------------

JJ: Looks like she is struggling with adherence, mostly.

Lin: Right. Let's have AI help brainstorm how we can help her.

JJ: I tried just asking "How can I improve adherence to the intervention plan?" but I got a really long, generic set of suggestions that wasn't very helpful. [face=explaining]

Lin: Well, that's because you didn't give it any context. We have to give enough background so it's giving advice on the problem we're actually trying to solve. Otherwise, it just fills in the blanks with general stuff that sounds reasonable but isn't really tailored to our needs. [face=serious]

JJ: What sort of context do we need?

Lianne: Well, you might want to make sure it knows that this is a psychology intervention using operant conditioning. And it really needs to know what plan you were following, and what specific problems Annie's roommate was having. [face=calm]

Annie: In short, we have to make everything explicit! Let's lay it all out this time. [face=smile]

::fba3_ai_adherence [display=target:psych_sba_sidebar4auto label="Ask AI About Adherence"]

--- wait @fba3_ai_adherence_response.value ---

